SIMPLE: welcome
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Welcome
<hw>Wel"come</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>welcome</ets>, <ets>welcume</ets>, <ets>wilcume</ets>, AS.
<ets>wilcuma</ets> a welcome guest, from <ets>wil-</ets>, as a prefix,
akin to <ets>willa</ets> will + <ets>cuma</ets> a comer, fr.
<ets>cuman</ets> to come; hence, properly, one who comes so as to please
another's will; cf. Icel. <ets>velkominn</ets> welcome, G.
<ets>willkommen</ets>. See <er>Will</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, and
Come.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Received with gladness; admitted willingly to the
house, entertainment, or company; <as>as, a <ex>welcome</ex>
visitor</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When the glad soul is made Heaven's <qex>welcome</qex> guest.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Producing gladness; grateful; <as>as, a
<ex>welcome</ex> present; <ex>welcome</ex> news</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧O,
<xex>welcome</xex> hour!⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Free to have or enjoy gratuitously; <as>as, you are
<ex>welcome</ex> to the use of my library</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Welcome</xex> is used elliptically for <xex>you are
welcome</xex>. ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Welcome</xex>, great monarch, to your
own.⟦rdquo⟧</note> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Welcome-to-our-house</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a
kind of spurge (<spn>Euphorbia Cyparissias</spn>).</cd> <rj><au>Dr.
Prior.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Welcome</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Welcome
<hw>Wel"come</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Salutation to a newcomer.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Welcome</xex> ever smiles.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Kind reception of a guest or newcomer; <as>as, we
entered the house and found a ready <ex>welcome</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His warmest <qex>welcome</qex> at an inn.</q>
<rj><qau>Shenstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Truth finds an entrance and a <qex>welcome</qex> too.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To bid welcome</b></col>, <cd>to receive with professions
of kindness.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To thee and thy company I <qex>bid</qex>⟦br⟧
A hearty <qex>welcome</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Welcome</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Welcome
<hw>Wel"come</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Welcomed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Welcoming</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS.
<ets>wilcumian</ets>.]</ety> <def>To salute with kindness, as a
newcomer; to receive and entertain hospitably and cheerfully; <as>as, to
<ex>welcome</ex> a visitor; to <ex>welcome</ex> a new idea</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧I <xex>welcome</xex> you to land.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thus we salute thee with our early song,⟦br⟧
And <qex>welcome</qex> thee, and wish thee long.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Welcomely</ent>⟦br⟧
